## About ScanVault

ScanVault is a privacy-first document scanner that keeps your data exactly where it belongs — on your device.

- **Complete Privacy** – 100% of your documents are saved locally on your device.
- **No Watermarks** – Clean, professional scans every time.
- **No Cloud Uploads** – Your files never leave your device without your explicit permission.
- **No Data Collection** – We respect your privacy; no usage tracking or data mining.
- **Easy to Use** – Simple, intuitive interface for quick scanning.

## Frequently Asked Questions

**Q: Where are my scanned documents stored?**
A: All documents are stored locally on your device. They are never uploaded to any server unless you choose to export or share them yourself.

**Q: Does ScanVault collect any personal data or usage analytics?**
A: No. ScanVault does not track usage or collect any personal data.

**Q: Why don't my scans have a watermark?**
A: Unlike many free scanning apps, ScanVault never adds watermarks to your documents — every scan is clean and professional.

**Q: How do I export or share a scanned document?**
A: Open the document in ScanVault and use the share/export option to save it to Files, email it, or send it to another app of your choice.

**Q: I found a bug or have a feature request. How do I report it?**
A: Please email us at **sts1245@live.com** with a description of the issue or request, and we'll get back to you as soon as possible.

**Q: How do I delete a scanned document?**
A: Open the document list, swipe or select the document you want to remove, and choose delete. Deleted documents are removed permanently from your device.

